{"TopicId":138566,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"unity default shaders- heat refraction- would it work","CreatedByName":"amankd","CreatedById":135588,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T17:18:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"amankd","CreatedById":135588,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T17:18:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthere is a default texture in unity called \u0022stainedbumpdistort that uses a normal map to distort, much like heat refractioon, how would i go about getting this shader to work in ksp? how can i load it? would it oload anyway?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T19:37:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou\u0027d need some plugin to load the shader. after that it could work but on a cone shaped mesh attached to the engine. Heat refraction effect are generally post effect shaders, similar to pixel shaders like the stained glass sample shader from unity5, but operate at a different point in the render pipeline.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-30T21:24:09Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2016 09:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by nli2work\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sashan","CreatedById":98897,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T21:07:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBahamutoD made it work somehow. Unfortunately, he never released it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/bnKJO2EHTVA?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0